   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Introducing data loaders and batches"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 100,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import patches\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "import torch.utils as utils\n",
    "import lettertask\n",
    "import torch.nn as nn\n",
    "import torch.optim as optim\n",
    "from tqdm import tqdm\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import plotnine as gg\n",
    "import lazytools_sflippl as lazytools\n",
    "import time\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import mizani.transforms as transforms"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 45,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cbm = lettertask.data.CompositionalBinaryModel(\n",
    "    width=[5, 5],\n",
    "    change_probability=[0.05, 0.5],\n",
    "    samples=10000,\n",
    "    seed=None\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 46,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cts = patches.data.Contrastive1DTimeSeries(cbm.to_array())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 47,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cdl = utils.data.DataLoader(cts, batch_size=16, drop_last=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 48,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ce = patches.networks.LinearScaffold(1, data=cts)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 51,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "criterion = patches.losses.ContrastiveLoss(loss=nn.MSELoss())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 52,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "similarity = patches.losses._NegExp(loss=nn.MSELoss())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 53,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "tensor(2.4833, grad_fn=<NegBackward>)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 53,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "criterion(x)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Seems to work!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 68,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ideal = np.array([1]*5+[0]*5)/np.sqrt(5)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 56,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "100%|██████████| 5/5 [00:11<00:00,  2.38s/it]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "optimizer = optim.Adam(ce.parameters())\n",
    "angles = []\n",
    "loss_traj = []\n",
    "running_loss = 0\n",
    "for epoch in tqdm(range(5)):\n",
    "    running_loss = 0\n",
    "    for i, data in enumerate(cdl):\n",
    "        if i<len(cdl):\n",
    "            if i % 10 == 0:\n",
    "                est = list(ce.parameters())[0].detach().numpy()\n",
    "                angles.append(np.matmul(ideal, est.T)/np.sqrt(np.matmul(est, est.T)))\n",
    "            optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
    "            code = ce(data)\n",
    "            loss = criterion(code)\n",
    "            loss.backward()\n",
    "            optimizer.step()\n",
    "            running_loss += loss\n",
    "            if i % 50 == 49:\n",
    "                loss_traj.append(running_loss.detach().numpy()/50)\n",
    "                running_loss = 0"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 61,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",

       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },

    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<ggplot: (-9223363298386779434)>"

     "execution_count": 61,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "(gg.ggplot(lazytools.array_to_dataframe(np.array(loss_traj)),\n",
    "           gg.aes(x='dim0', y='array')) +\n",
    "    gg.geom_line())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 59,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",

   "source": [
    "(gg.ggplot(lazytools.array_to_dataframe(np.array(angles)),\n",

   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Exploring different batch sizes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 66,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "4096"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 66,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "2**12"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 76,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "5.122344017028809"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 76,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "time.time()-start"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 135,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Starting batch size 1\n",
      "Starting batch size 2\n",
      "Starting batch size 4\n",
      "Starting batch size 8\n",
      "Starting batch size 16\n",
      "Starting batch size 32\n",
      "Starting batch size 64\n",
      "Starting batch size 128\n",
      "Starting batch size 256\n",
      "Starting batch size 512\n",
      "Starting batch size 1024\n",
      "Starting batch size 2048\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "loss_dfs = []\n",
    "angle_dfs = []\n",
    "batch_sizes = range(12)\n",
    "for batch_size in batch_sizes:\n",
    "    cdl = utils.data.DataLoader(cts, batch_size=2**batch_size, drop_last=True)\n",
    "    ce = patches.networks.LinearScaffold(1, data=cts)\n",
    "    optimizer = optim.Adam(ce.parameters(), lr=0.01)\n",
    "    angles = []\n",
    "    loss_traj = []\n",
    "    running_loss = 0\n",
    "    print('Starting batch size {}'.format(2**batch_size))\n",
    "    start = time.time()\n",
    "    while (time.time()-start) < 2:\n",
    "        running_loss = 0\n",
    "        for i, data in enumerate(cdl):\n",
    "            if i<len(cdl):\n",
    "                if i % np.ceil(10/(2**batch_size)) == 0:\n",
    "                    est = list(ce.parameters())[0].detach().numpy()\n",
    "                    angles.append(np.matmul(ideal, est.T)/np.sqrt(np.matmul(est, est.T)))\n",
    "                optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
    "                code = ce(data)\n",
    "                loss = criterion(code)\n",
    "                loss.backward()\n",
    "                optimizer.step()\n",
    "                running_loss += loss\n",
    "                if i % np.ceil(50/(2**batch_size)) == np.ceil(50/(2**batch_size))-1:\n",
    "                    loss_traj.append(running_loss.detach().numpy()/\n",
    "                                     np.ceil(50/(2**batch_size)))\n",
    "                    running_loss = 0\n",
    "    stop = time.time()-start\n",
    "    loss_df = lazytools.array_to_dataframe(np.array(loss_traj))\\\n",
    "                       .rename(columns={'dim0': 'steps', 'array': 'loss'})\n",
    "    loss_df['steps'] *= stop/loss_df['steps'].max()\n",
    "    loss_df['batch_size'] = np.array(2**batch_size)\n",
    "    angle_df = lazytools.array_to_dataframe(np.array(angles))\\\n",
    "                        .rename(columns={'dim0': 'steps', 'array': 'angle'})\n",
    "    angle_df['steps'] *= stop/angle_df['steps'].max()\n",
    "    angle_df['batch_size'] = np.array(2**batch_size)\n",
    "    loss_dfs.append(loss_df)\n",
    "    angle_dfs.append(angle_df)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 136,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df_loss = pd.concat(loss_dfs)\n",
    "df_angle = pd.concat(angle_dfs)"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's dive further into the area between 8 and 16. Clearly we should not overfit, but it is interesting to explore how smooth the angle can actually be. Also note that this does not disadvantage large batches since one step always represents about one second."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 140,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "del df_loss\n",
    "del df_angle"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 141,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Starting batch size 8\n",
      "Starting batch size 9\n",

      "Starting batch size 11\n",
      "Starting batch size 12\n",
      "Starting batch size 13\n",
      "Starting batch size 14\n",
      "Starting batch size 15\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "loss_dfs = []\n",
    "angle_dfs = []\n",
    "batch_sizes = range(8, 16)\n",
    "for batch_size in batch_sizes:\n",
    "    cdl = utils.data.DataLoader(cts, batch_size=batch_size, drop_last=True)\n",
    "    ce = patches.networks.LinearScaffold(1, data=cts)\n",
    "    optimizer = optim.Adam(ce.parameters(), lr=0.01)\n",
    "    angles = []\n",
    "    loss_traj = []\n",
    "    running_loss = 0\n",
    "    print('Starting batch size {}'.format(batch_size))\n",
    "    start = time.time()\n",
    "    while (time.time()-start) < 2:\n",
    "        running_loss = 0\n",
    "        for i, data in enumerate(cdl):\n",
    "            if i<len(cdl):\n",
    "                if i % np.ceil(10/(2**batch_size)) == 0:\n",
    "                    est = list(ce.parameters())[0].detach().numpy()\n",
    "                    angles.append(np.matmul(ideal, est.T)/np.sqrt(np.matmul(est, est.T)))\n",
    "                optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
    "                code = ce(data)\n",
    "                loss = criterion(code)\n",
    "                loss.backward()\n",
    "                optimizer.step()\n",
    "                running_loss += loss\n",
    "                if i % np.ceil(50/(batch_size)) == np.ceil(50/(batch_size))-1:\n",
    "                    loss_traj.append(running_loss.detach().numpy()/\n",
    "                                     np.ceil(50/(batch_size)))\n",
    "                    running_loss = 0\n",
    "    stop = time.time()-start\n",
    "    loss_df = lazytools.array_to_dataframe(np.array(loss_traj))\\\n",
    "                       .rename(columns={'dim0': 'steps', 'array': 'loss'})\n",
    "    loss_df['steps'] *= stop/loss_df['steps'].max()\n",
    "    loss_df['batch_size'] = np.array(batch_size)\n",
    "    angle_df = lazytools.array_to_dataframe(np.array(angles))\\\n",
    "                        .rename(columns={'dim0': 'steps', 'array': 'angle'})\n",
    "    angle_df['steps'] *= stop/angle_df['steps'].max()\n",
    "    angle_df['batch_size'] = np.array(batch_size)\n",
    "    loss_dfs.append(loss_df)\n",
    "    angle_dfs.append(angle_df)"
   ]
  },
